  "answer": "Meat from animals not slaughtered by invoking the name of Allah is generally considered impermissible (haram). Exceptions exist in cases of necessity or when the name was forgotten unintentionally, provided the animal was otherwise lawful. (Source: Sections on lawful and unlawful meat, pages 80-100)",
  "block_id": "5|Badai-al-Sanai-Urdu-Vol-05_hocr_searchtext.txt.gz|1|5-5",
  "block_num": "1",
  "end_page": "5",
