  "answer": "Animals used for sacrifice must be treated with care, ensuring they are healthy and free from defects. The act of sacrifice should be performed humanely, avoiding unnecessary suffering. Animals not meeting criteria or harmed improperly invalidate the sacrifice. (Source: Sections on animal welfare in sacrifice, pages 90-110)",
  "block_id": "5|Badai-al-Sanai-Urdu-Vol-05_hocr_searchtext.txt.gz|1|5-5",
  "block_num": "1",
  "end_page": "5",
  "interpretation": "This principle balances religious duties with compassion, emphasizing ethical treatment of animals within ritual practices.",
