  "answer": "Qabd, or possession, is essential for the validity of a sale. The buyer must take possession of the sold item, or the seller must deliver it, for the sale to be complete. Without possession, the sale may be considered incomplete or void. (Sections on possession and sale completion)",
  "block_id": "5|Badai-al-Sanai-Urdu-Vol-05_hocr_searchtext.txt.gz|3|7-7",
  "block_num": "3",
  "end_page": "7",
  "interpretation": "This principle ensures that ownership transfer is tangible and clear, preventing disputes over property rights.",
